# Notes for Course 1 on Feb.23

### Topic 1: Gene and genome
- gene: whose basis is information
- the central dogma: information propagation

Base pairs are the code for life, while not big genomes mean evolutionary advance.

A counter-intuitive fact: 
nearly 3/4 of the genome is transcribed, most of which are previously considered useless. 
Many RNA molecules are synthesized with potential functions. lncRNAs are now thought to carry out important functions.

### Topic 2: Sequencing technologies 
- undergo revolution in recent years.
- provide big and high-dimension data

### Topic 3: What do bioinformatics do?
-Data Problems:
  -Representation (graphics) 
  -Storage and retrieval (databases) 
  -Analysis method (statistics, artificial intelligence, optimization, etc.) 
-Biology Problems: 
  -Interpreting biological sequences
  -Predicting structure or function
  -Mining clinical (i.e. cancer) data/information

### Topic 4: 3 steps for bioinformatics

Information --> model --> algorithms

在我看来，model是对于某一具体问题的内在数学关系和逻辑关系的概括，尊重客观事实，并随着不同概念的提出而不断做出修正。model很大程度上基于数学，尤其是概率和统计学的内容。<br>
而algorithm则是问题的具体解决方案，强调解决问题的清晰指令和策略要求，应当具有一定的普适性和适应性。algorithm应当是基于计算科学，追求更高的效率和过程的简明。<br>
我认为model和algorithm应该是解决问题的不同阶段所使用的工具和方法论.<br>
model往往被用于描述问题，帮助其他研究者快速理清问题的本质，构建起清晰的框架，经得起实践的检验；<br>
而algorithm则是认清问题后总结出的“解题范式”，具有归并和统筹的潜力，帮助研究者举一反三，在实践中不断优化，取得更高的效率和更广阔的应用范围。
